@NODE "ToolTypes" "ToolTypes"


@{FG SHINE} NO_STARTUP_WINDOW @{FG TEXT}
   Allows you to start PfPaint without the startup requester.


@{FG SHINE} CLASSIC @{FG TEXT}
   By default, this tooltype is disable.
   This Tooltype will change the WorkSpace of Perfectpaint.
   Disable 'Classic' will show you only the zoom window (like other Processing software)
   Enable 'Classic' will show you for each picture the main window (always 100%) and
   optionnaly the Zoom window (like other version of PfPaint).


@{FG SHINE} PICASSO96 @{FG TEXT}
   Use this tooltype if you have problem 
   while displaying brush or text in zoom window.
   (PfPaint will disable the cybergraphics command scalepixelarray_ and
   will improve compatibility with Picasso96)


@{FG SHINE} CYBERGRAPHX @{FG TEXT}
   Force PfPaint to detect Cybergraphx


@{FG SHINE} SCREEN_ID @{FG TEXT}
@{FG SHINE} SCREEN_WIDTH @{FG TEXT}
@{FG SHINE} SCREEN_HEIGHT @{FG TEXT}
@{FG SHINE} SCREEN_DEPTH @{FG TEXT}
   Some user can't open the startup requester or can't open
   the screenmode requester ( I really don't know why ?)
   so these tooltypes are for them.
   
   SCREEN_ID                ID of the screen
   SCREEN_WIDTH             Width of the screen (min 640)
   SCREEN_HEIGHT            Height of the screen (min 480)
   SCREEN_DEPTH             Depth of the screen (15,16 or 24bits)

   ex:
   SCREEN_ID=40d20040 (Use 'GetHexModeID' to know ID of a screen)
   SCREEN_WIDTH=800
   SCREEN_HEIGHT=600
   SCREEN_DEPTH=24

@ENDNODE

@NODE "FenUR" "Undo-Redo Window"

@{" Picture " link "picture/URWin.jpg/Main" 0}

You can activate this window with the 'Undo-Redo/Show Undo-Redo window' item, under the Undo button.

This window will show you all actions made on the picture.
You can easily navigate from one step of the picture to another step by clicking over an action
in the window.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "FenHis" "Fenetre d'Historique"

@{" Image " link "picture/HisWin.jpg/Main" 0}

You can activate this window with the 'Picture/Show history' item.

This window will show you all loading and saving picture you made.(max 100)
For each file PfPaint will keep the path, name, size and preview of the picture.

Menu:
   Clear: Will clear the current files from the history.
   Clear history: Will clear all files in the history window.
   Visual requester: Will show you all files by preview.
   Prefs: will show you the pref requester of the history.

Gadget:
  On/Off gadget
  Info: Will show you some informations of the selected files.
  Load: Will show you a loading requester with path and name of the selected files.
  Save: Will show you a saving requester with path and name of the selected files.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "PalIm" "Image Palette"

The image palette will show you all the 10 buffers.
These buffers can be pictures or animations.

@{FG SHINE}RMB @{FG TEXT}on a thumbnail will show you the size and depth of the buffer.
@{FG SHINE}LMB @{FG TEXT}on a thumbnail will activate the selected buffer.

@{FG SHINE}LMB @{FG TEXT}over the trashcan button to erase the current buffer.
@{FG SHINE}LMB @{FG TEXT}over the brush icon to open the brush palette.

@{BG SHINE} With Shift+LMB ,you can Drag and Drop: @{BG BACK}

@{FG SHINE}Drag and Drop @{FG TEXT}a thumbnail over the current picture to compose with an optional opacity.
(stencil of the two pictures can be used)

@{FG SHINE}Drag and Drop @{FG TEXT}a thumbnail over another thumbnail to clone the picture.
@{FG SHINE}Drag and Drop @{FG TEXT}a thumbnail over the trashcan to erase the selected buffer.

@{FG SHINE}Drag and Drop @{FG TEXT}a thumbnail over the brush icon to convert the picture into brush.
@{FG SHINE}Drag and Drop @{FG TEXT}the brush icon over a thumbnail to convert the brush into picture.
@{FG SHINE}Drag and Drop @{FG TEXT}the brush icon over the trashcan to erase it.


@ENDNODE
