@NODE "SBox" "Box"

@{B}AnimPainting_Box.rx@{UB}
  Simulates AnimPainting with the Box tool.
  You need to create an animation beforehand.
  The box will be drawn throughout the length of the animation.

@{B}Funny_Border.rx@{UB}
  Several ways to draw a border.
 
@ENDNODE
@NODE "SCircle" "Circle"

@{B}AnimPainting_Circle.rx@{UB}
  Simulates Animpainting with the Circle tool.
  You have to choose the circle's direction of rotation.
  You need to create an animation beforehand.
  The circle will be drawn throughout the length of the animation.

@{B}AnimPainting_Circle_Whirl.rx@{UB}
  Simulates Animpainting with the Circle tool.
  You have to choose the circle's direction of rotation.
  The circle will be drawn starting from its centre.
  You need to create an animation beforehand.
  The circle will be drawn throughout the length of the animation.

@{B}Anim_Pulsar.rx@{UB}
  Creates a pulsar effect (an expanding circle).
  You need to create an animation beforehand.

@{B}Make_AnimStar.rx@{UB}
  This script will create a star. You may choose the number of
  points it has and whether it is empty or filled.
  Then the star will be drawn on each frame of the animation,
  rotating through 90° throughout the animation's length.
  You need to create an animation beforehand.

@{B}Star.rx@{UB}
  This script will create a star. You may choose the number of
  points it has and whether it is empty or filled.

@{B}Total_Circle.rx@{UB}
  This script will create a circle with the specified number of points.

@{B}Sun.rx@{UB}
 This script will create a cartoon's sun.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SEllipse" "Ellipse"

@{B}AnimPainting_Ellipse.rx@{UB}
  Simulates AnimPainting with the Ellipse tool.
  You have to choose the ellipse's direction of rotation.
  You need to create an animation beforehand.
  The ellipse will be drawn throughout the length of the animation.

@{B}Make_Star.rx@{UB}
  This script will create a star. You may choose the number of
  points it has and whether it is empty or filled.

@{B}Total_Ellipse.rx@{UB}
  This script will create an ellipse with the specified number of points.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SSpline" "Spline"

@{B}AnimPainting_Spline.rx@{UB}
  Simulates AnimPainting with the Spline tool.
  You need to create an animation beforehand.
  The spline will be drawn throughout the length of the animation.

@{B}Total_Spline.rx@{UB}
  This script will create a spline with the specified number of points.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SGeneral" "General"

@{B}FadeInBlack.rx@{UB}
  This script will fade an animation to black.
  You must specify the start and end frames, and whether it
  should fade in or out.

@{B}SaveAnimGif.rx@{UB}
  Saves the current animation in AnimGIF format.

@{B}SaveGif_Brush.rx@{UB}
  Saves the current brush in GIF format.

@{B}SaveGif_Picture.rx@{UB}
  Saves the current picture in GIF format.

@{B}SaveNewIcon.rx@{UB}
  Takes the two supplied brushed and creates a NewIcon.
  This script needs the executable 'Injectbrush' in your C: directory.

@{B}Warp.rx@{UB}
  Uses the current picture to create a 10-frame animation, performing
  a random warp on each frame. The animation is then played.

@{B}Communication with ADPro@{UB}
  LoadADPro_Brush.rx
  LoadADPro_Picture.rx
  SaveADPro_Brush.rx
  SaveADPro_Picture.rx

@ENDNODE
@NODE "SLine" "Line"

@{B}AnimPainting_Line.rx@{UB}
  Simulates AnimPainting with the Line tool.
  You need to create an animation beforehand.
  The line will be drawn throughout the length of the animation.

@{B}Funny_Line.rx@{UB}
  Several ways to plot a line.

@{B}Line_Measure.rx@{UB}
  Gives the exact length of a line.

@{B}Angle repare.rx@{UB}  

@{B}Arrow.rx@{UB}
 Make Arrows.
@ENDNODE
@NODE "port" "Arexx Port"

The Arexx port may be accessed in different ways.

If the script is started from within PerfectPaint, the first parameter
passed to the script is the name of the port to use.

Example:
    /* Title of script*/
     Options results
     parse ARG Port ..... b
     ADDRESS value Port
     .....
         

There are many ways to execute a script from PerfectPaint:

@{FG SHINE}In the simplest way, the script is not associated with any tool.@{FG TEXT}

Example:
    /* Title of script*/
     Options results
     parse ARG Port b
        ADDRESS value Port    
     ......


@{FG SHINE}If the script is associated with a tool:@{FG TEXT}

        @{B}Line:@{UB}@{FG TEXT}
            parse ARG Port x1 y1 x2 y2 b
          /* x1, y1: co-ordinates of the start of the line
             x2, y2: co-ordinates of the end of the line */

        @{B}Circle:@{UB}@{FG TEXT}
          parse ARG Port x1 y1 r b
          /* x1, y1: co-ordinates of the centre of the circle
             r: the circle's radius */

        @{B}Box:@{UB}@{FG TEXT}
          parse ARG Port x1 y1 x2 y2 b
          /* x1, y1: top-left corner of the box
             x2, y2: bottom-right corner of the box */
  
        @{B}Ellipse:@{UB}
          parse ARG Port x1 y1 r1 r2 b
          /* x1, y1: centre of the ellipse
             r1, r2: the ellipse's radii */

        @{B}Point:@{UB}
          parse ARG Port x1 y1 b
          /* x1, y1: co-ordinates of the point */

        @{B}Spline:@{UB}
          parse ARG Port x1 y1 x2 y2 x3 y3 b
          /* x1, y1: Co-ordinates of the start of the spline
             x2, y2: Co-ordinates of the end of the spline 
             x3, y3: Point of curvature */ 


@{FG SHINE}If the script is associated with the Bridge function:@{FG TEXT}

          parse ARG Port1 Port2 b
          /* Port1: Source port
             Port2: Destination port */ 

__________________________________________________________________________
@{FG SHINE}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{FG TEXT}
    
@{FG SHINE}If the script is not started by Perfectpaint, an instance of PerfectPaint
must be searched for and its port found.@{FG TEXT}

Example:
    /* Script name */

     found=0
     Port="Perfect_Paint."
     DO i=1 to 7
        IF SHOW('P',Port||i) THEN DO
           Port=Port||i
           found=1
           LEAVE
        END
     END

    if found=0 then EXIT
     /* No instances of PerfectPaint are running, so quit */

     ADDRESS value Port 
    ...

__________________________________________________________________________
@{FG SHINE}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{FG TEXT}

If a script is called 'StartUp.rx' and is found in the PerfectPaint drawer
along with the main program, this script will be executed at startup.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "H17" "V2.91"

- A lot of new keyboard shortcuts
- Improve for Animation:
  Crop - Scale - Scale page
	Color correction - Gamma - Negative - ScrollRGB - Swap RGB
- Remove some requester when arexx is on.
- Numeric keyboard to select brush (0-9)
- Preview effect for very small picture is fixed
- Minimum, maximum and median effect works well now for very small picture
- Improve creation of Animation when several pictures are dropped into the appicon.
- Improve drawing effect: Colorize
- Add Brush Handle (Alt x)
- New picture effect: Mirror
- 'Ctrl' can be used now to block cursor in X or Y position
- Improve addframe,delete frame and copy frame: Jiffies are now respected.
- New animation effect:
		- Double each frame
			All frames will be duplicated with a mix option.
		- Cel Number:This script places the cel number on each selected frame. 
			Prefix and suffix can be assigned 
- Insert picture work correcty now with indexed palette
- New Arexx command:
	pp_RemapBrush
	pp_SetRGBcolor
	pp_PickColor, pp_GetPickRed,pp_GetPick_Green,pp_GetPickGreen
	pp_AddFrames
	pp_TextGui
	pp_FixBrush
- Convert to RGB and Convert to CMAP works now with animation
- Improve Text_Gui and palette requester
- Add an 'Info Button' on Some requester.
- Show Grid works now in "non classic" mode.
- New picture item: Erase All Buffers (K)
- And always several little bug fixed.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "H16" "V2.9"

- New drawing effect: TV Lace
- New Arexx Command: pp_TVLace

- Improve text: 
    PfPaint can now read TrueType fonts with the help of ttengine.library
    (you have to install it)

		Add 2 new buttons: - Select Character (very useful for Dingbats fonts)
	                     - Font path history.
		Add 2 new item in the requester menu: Upper text and Lower text

- litle update for the script 'Lensflare'

- New asynchron window: Undo/Redo
  You can easily jump from one step of the picture to another step.

- Some Bug corrected

- Size Presets added to the 'New' requester and 'Scale page' requester

- added AutoCrop (include in the 'crop' requester. 

- PfPaint will Detect automatically
     PGM picture and load it.
     PS or PDF file, and try to load it with the help of ghostscript

- Improve text effect "Azzaro"
- 2 New text effect: Water and River)

- improve window history
- fix a bug with picbrush tool and very big picture
- 5 new tooltypes
  SCREEN_ID
  SCREEN_WIDTH
  SCREEN_HEIGHT
  SCREEN_DEPTH
    Some people can't open the startup requester or can't open
	  the screenmode requester ( I really don't know why ?)
	  so these tooltypes are for them.

	CYBERGRAPHX: Force PfPaint to detect Cybergraphx

- Limit Border&Edge to 24bits picture
- Improve 'Compose' requester
- New Item in the 'Picture' menu "Crop & Paste"
- Improve "Adjust levels" with an editable tolerance

@ENDNODE

